message.content:
cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses users' behavior in online communities and proposes a probabilistic model to capture different levels of steering. The paper also applies this model to data from the Q&A site, Stack Overflow. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) likely categories. The study of users' behavior in online communities also involves human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the motivation of users to contribute to online communities, which can be related to information retrieval and recommendation systems, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
